Dialogue:
Take me, but
leave the lunches!

The docks... You must...
secure the... \\<cough>

Perhaps this isn't the
best place to hide...
Go on, then! Knock some sense into them!

See that it
gets done, then.

Ye try spittin' that bilge
before the guildmaster.

Come summer, I'll be
runnin' these here docks.

You chose the
right man for the job!

That'll be a holt's worth
of lumber down there.

Take care to stand
clear of the edge.
Ah, the smell of the sea!

Perhaps if you stopped
yapping and helped me
look, we'd find the man.

Lookin' for work? The
offices are further down.

And what would you
know about beauty?

A few more days in the
sun and they'll be ready.

Been nibblin' on yer
arse again, have they?

Oi! Where'd you
want these nails, lads?

Then ye'll jus' 'ave to
knock some into 'im!

That new hand hasn't
a single wit about him!

Take them sacks to
the storehouse. And
stop starin' at me arse.

Get your fresh fruit!
Keep the scurvy at bay!

Come and have a
taste of Aleport's finest!

The flames gone singed
every last hair on me head!

Ye'd reckon thirty crates
o' tar'd be more 'an enough.

Where in the seven
hells is my damn ship!?

Shut yer gob and
move that arse.

Someone should tell
that poor Sea Wolf.

The Drydocks are
closed for repairs today.

I'm tired of repairin'
leaky galleys all day.
Aye! When do we start workin' on the Victory?

Don't let Mimidoa
hear you say that!

I have me a son.
Isaac's his name.

I swear if he
touches me again,
I'll cut off his hand!

That's not all what
deserves a cuttin'!

Or, just early for
the morrow's work.
What ye needs is to lay off the ale.

I needs me a ship so
I might see the world.

Sure it wasn't just
your reflection?

I saw a Sahagin right
over there. I swear it!

I suppose this'll
have to do for now.

This here crate reeks
of rotting fish and old tar.

Put yer back into it,
ye nine-stone ninny!

Leviathan's eye! What'd
they fill this bugger with!?

Wha? Me gil's not
good enough fer ye?

I cannot say. But
that won't stop me
from trying.

Wavin' yer hand like
that ain't gonna make
it any less hot.

You play cards about as
well as you comb your hair.

You didn't forget the
leves again, did you?

This gate is to
remain closed.

Where ever did
you find that tunic?

Pah! I saw you swipe it
from a stall in Stonesthrow!

Now where did he
hide that letter!?

This place is deader
than a lichyard.

They're all so stunning.
I simply cannot decide!

Keep those filthy gropers
off the merchandise, you.

And doing so could
improve productivity
threefold!

I'm to see no harm
comes to his lordship as
he inspects the hammers.

And when the Brass
Blade is turned away─

Well, maybe if you hadn't
downed that last bottle...

Impossible! I calibrated
them myself this morning!

I believe the gears are
showing signs of slowing.

Back to work, or I'll
dock another hundred gil!

A wanderin' minstrel
gave me this here pipe.

What were if I waved
it right crackin', like?

Ye said I'd be gettin'
fifty fer each load!

These feel lighter
than they should...

Where the hells is that
rattling coming from?

Move yer arse, so I can
set this bugger down.

That was last week.
Today, I can offer you six.

Thirty crates, delivered
by dawn. Just as ordered.

No, no! This will not do!
The wheels will have to
be replaced forthwith!

And the miner said, “But
I don't have a daughter!”
Did I just see what I thought I saw?

You'll not get a gil more
than what was agreed upon!

I got you here a full bell
early. I'm thinkin' that be
worth another hundred.

Two hundred and
fifty-two, you half-wit!

I run a business, not an
almshouse. If it is coin
you seek, get a job.

I should've learned to
play the mandolin...

You heard what became
of the last party!

Aye, but what choice
do we have?

The Concern decides
who may pass.

You don't want
to go back there.

I'm thinking of courting
that assessor. The one
who ties her hair up, like.
一ケタ間違えちゃったかも…

Zzz... Zzz... Zzz...
Zzz... Wark? Zzz...

There are no beasts
trailing you, are there?

I cannot allow you to
leave until your cargo
has been inspected.

Thal's balls, this is
heavier than an aurochs!
で、ブツはいつ届くんだ？
愚痴は掘った穴に叫べよ

Copperbell's done
for, I tell ye.

If I told you once, I've
told you a thousand times!

Touch anything, and
Bloody Catapult here
will tear your arms off.

Sign there...there...there...
and there......oh, and there.

The assessors' office
lies in the rear.

Perhaps a coin or two
could speed things up.

Get the birds out
of here! Now!
給料分は守ってやるか

Never again will I assay
the ride from Gridania
in a single turn of the sun.

I've my eye on each
and every one of this
unsavory lot!

Come over here and say
that, you baseborn dog!

Two days!? We
cannot wait that long!

I swear that bloody sun's
hotter since the Calamity.

Sleeping!? I was merely
shielding my eyes from
the sun!

Yalik senleh...ahamat
zah... Or is it jah...?

Quickly now, lads!
We haven't all day.

The entrance must
be here somewhere!

Could we not simply hire
a few urchins from
Stonesthrow to do this?

Hand me that lan─
Oh, another adventurer...

I should have left my
robe back at the Ossuary.

I see naught
but a pile o' rubble.

Only if I can
have the eyes!

The Spinner pulls, but
the Wanderer pushes away.

A barrel full o' bream;
a pocket full o' naught.

These should fetch a
fine price at the markets.

Get it your Twelve-
damned self, you lazy
son of a mutt.

Don't let your da hear
you talk that nonsense!

When I grow up, I want
to be a cully-narian!
One lousy night in the salting house, and me whole body reeks o' cod!

Have any ale on you?
No? Then bugger off.
Not another turn of the sun in this piss'ole...

Mimilo's husband fell
asleep in the salting
house last night...

Hah hah hah! Who says
I needs me a man?

I'm more man than
you'll ever need, lass!

Sittin' here in Vesper
Bay, watchin' the
'bos ride away...♪

Keep your weapons
sheathed or you'll have
me to answer to.

You look awfully...sober.
Might be we can fix that.

Used to be there was
two moons, there was.

The captain claims
he found nothing.

But I know I had the ring
when I boarded in Limsa!

I'd work if there were
work to be had...

I'll be eatin' like
a little lord tonight!

If I boil the leather
from these soles...

Tell them the first pinch
is on you. Understood?

Ain't no laws 'gainst
cultivatin' the soil.

My mother holds her
drink better than you!

I could drink this
whole tank, I could!

But the air down there...
It's makin' 'em ill.

Tell the men they
must dig deeper!

I don't have the heart
to tell the lads that
was the last bottle...

Used to be a man might
make a decent livin' off
minin' copper alone.

Through the pass is
Bluefog...and an army
of damned imperials.

If I never see another
shrew again it'll be too soon.

We must've slain what,
nine or ten score?

We are the last line of
defense before Ul'dah's
last line of defense!
Stay sharp, men!
個人取引はしてないぞ
Not too tight, is it, boy?

I believe we'll be
needing another chocobo.

What? Never seen a
man in an apron afore?

No, but I wouldn't mind
seein' you out of one!

Never let them
see your fear!

If I catch you stealing,
I'll cut off more than
just your hand.

Best you not wander
far from camp... If you
value your life, that is.

Here by the aetheryte all
day... When will I get to
see some real fighting?

Always keep an eye open.
The Empire never sleeps.

Eat, man! Ye cannae
right kill an imperial
on an empty belly, now!

Are you so eager to get
your head on a pike over
Castrum Meridianum?

Why do we stand here
idly while the Empire
gathers strength?

Bugger off. I need
to concentrate!

Not here to relieve
us, are you?

Quiet! I cannot see with
all your yapping!

Don't tell the sergeant, but
without my spectacles, I
cannot see worth shite.

How I long to be back
in Ul'dah with my wife...

If you had any wits
about you, you'd turn back.

Absolutely no entry to
unauthorized personnel.

I should really learn to
read one of these days.
ピリピリしてんだ、ほっとけ

Yer mother was an
imperial whore!

Aye, and she still
wouldn't take yer coin!

Twenty-eight, twen─ Oh!
Would you stop interrupting?
Now I'll have to start again!

You didn't happen to
see a caravan on your
way here, did you?

Not today. Not yester-
day. Not the day before...

If the imperials don't
kill you, the fog will.

Don't wait for your oppo-
nent! Strike him down
before he strikes you!

Your safety cannot be
guaranteed once you
leave these gates.

If you see an imperial,
let us know so that we
may sound the alarm.

You'll find little respite
beyond this gate.

We're now a sennight
behind schedule.

The foreman'll have
our arses on a stick.

What say we make our
rounds widdershins?
To break the monotony.

Death cannot break
the bonds between us.

How am I to pay off your
debts now, husband!?
